DAY 3: Directory Operations

Creating, Navigating, and Managing Directories

## Commands

1. mkdir – Make Directories
2. rmdir – Remove Empty Directories
3. cd – Change Directory
4. stat – Display File/Directory Status

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Mkdir - Flag Description 

-p Create parent directories as needed (no error if exists)
-v Verbose – print message for each created directory
-m MODE Set permission mode (like chmod)

cd - Flag Description
-c FORMAT Use custom format for output
-f Display file system status
-L Follow symbolic links
-t Print in terse form

Usage Description
cd Go to home directory
cd ~ Go to home directory
cd - Go to previous directory
cd .. Go to parent directory
cd ../.. Go up two levels
cd /path Go to absolute path
cd ./dir Go to relative path




## Examples

# Create single directory

$ mkdir projects
$ ls
projects

# Create multiple directories
$ mkdir dir1 dir2 dir3
$ ls
dir1 dir2 dir3 projects

# Create nested directories ( parent + child )
$ mkdir -p projects / webapp / src / main
$ tree projects
projects

webapp
src
main

# Create with verbose output
$ mkdir -v test1 test2
mkdir : created directory ’ test1 ’
mkdir : created directory ’ test2 ’

# Create with specific permissions
$ mkdir -m 755 public_folder
$ mkdir -m 700 private_folder
$ ls -l
drwxr - xr - x 2 raman raman 4096 Jan 15 10:00 public_folder
drwx - - - - - - 2 raman raman 4096 Jan 15 10:00 private_folder

# Create complex structure
$ mkdir - pv project / { src , bin , docs , tests }
mkdir : created directory ’ project ’
mkdir : created directory ’ project / src ’
mkdir : created directory ’ project / bin ’
mkdir : created directory ’ project / docs ’
mkdir : created directory ’ project / tests ’


# Remove empty directory
$ rmdir empty_folder

# Remove with verbose
$ rmdir -v test_dir
rmdir : removing directory , ’ test_dir ’

# Remove nested empty directories
$ mkdir -p a / b / c
$ rmdir - pv a / b / c
rmdir : removing directory , ’a / b /c ’
rmdir : removing directory , ’a /b ’
rmdir : removing directory , ’a ’

# Error if directory not empty
$ rmdir documents
rmdir : failed to remove ’ documents ’: Directory not empty



# Go to home directory
$ cd
$ pwd
/ home / raman

$ cd ~
$ pwd
/ home / raman

# Go to specific directory
$ cd / var / log
$ pwd
/ var / log

# Go to parent directory
$ cd ..
$ pwd
/ var

# Go up two levels
$ cd .. / ..
$ pwd
/

# Go to previous directory
$ cd / etc
$ cd / var / log
$ cd -
/ etc

# Relative paths
$ cd ~ / Documents
$ cd . / projects
$ cd .. / Downloads


